Summary: nothing in first picture, then appears and moves in next 2 (10 seconds)
divs: Sighting DetailsWas taking cloud pictures with wife and took three in a 10 second period. First one shows nothing, then object appears in second shot, and then moves slightly lower in third. Didn't see anything until I looked at the shots right after, because of distance I didn't see anything until looking at the pictures. After tried to see if I could recreate shot, but no luck. We both thought that the object was solid, and not a flare, and the fact that it appeared in the 10 seconds I took the shots from one pic to the next is something we cant explain. No vapor trail or anything...it just appeared. I have never experienced anything like this...hopefully someone can tell me what this is.
